    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between Soudal Fix ALL and silicone sealant?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>Fix ALL</strong> is based on Soudal's SMX Hybrid Polymer technology, which combines the best properties of silicone and polyurethane. Unlike standard silicone, Fix ALL can be painted over, has superior adhesion to a wider range of substrates, and offers both sealing and bonding in one product. Silicone sealants remain the better choice for sanitary applications where anti-mould protection is the priority.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What types of expanding foam does Soudal offer?",
            "answer": "<p>Soudal is the world's largest independent PU foam producer and offers a comprehensive range. The <strong>Genius Gun</strong> hand-held system provides single-handed precision application and is re-sealable for up to 6 weeks. <strong>Professional gun-grade foams</strong> are available for high-volume applications. <strong>Fire-rated B1 foams</strong> provide certified fire protection around service penetrations. Specialist options include low-expansion foams for window and door frames.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can Soudal products be applied in cold weather?",
            "answer": "<p>Most Soudal sealants and adhesives can be applied at temperatures as low as <strong>5\u00b0C</strong>, with some products in the Fix ALL range workable down to <strong>-10\u00b0C</strong>. PU expanding foams require a minimum can temperature of around 5\u00b0C for optimal expansion. In cold conditions, store cans at room temperature before use and check the product datasheet for specific temperature guidelines.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Soudal products?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Soudal range including Fix ALL, Genius Gun foams and professional sealants. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. We also provide free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Which Fix ALL variant should I use?",
            "answer": "<p>The Fix ALL range includes several variants for different applications. <strong>Fix ALL High Tack</strong> (320kg/10cm\u00b2) is best for heavy-duty bonding where maximum strength is needed. <strong>Fix ALL Flexi</strong> is ideal as a multi-use sealant, adhesive and filler with high flexibility. <strong>Fix ALL Turbo</strong> provides rapid strength build-up and is fixed in 20 minutes. <strong>Fix ALL Crystal</strong> is the choice for applications where a clear, invisible bond is required.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the Soudal Genius Gun and how does it work?",
            "answer": "<p>The <strong>Genius Gun</strong> is Soudal's patented hand-held PU foam applicator. It features a trigger mechanism for precise, single-handed dosage control \u2014 no separate foam gun required. The key advantage is the re-sealable applicator, which allows the can to be reused for <strong>up to 6 weeks</strong> after first use. Available in standard gap filler and fire-rated B1 versions.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
